headline: Accenture (ACN): Reassessing Valuation After a Recent Share Price Rebound
summary: Accenture (ACN) has quietly staged a recovery over the past month, climbing about 13% even as its year to date return remains negative. That divergence is catching investors attention again. See our latest analysis for Accenture. The latest bounce has pushed Accenture’s share price to about $272. However, the strong 30 day and 90 day share price returns sit against a still negative year to date share price performance and modest multi year total shareholder returns.
